The RSCU values of MARVs and its two hosts, H. sapiens and R. aegyptiacus, were compared to determine influence of the host. The codon usage data of H. sapiens and R. aegyptiacus were obtained from the Codon Usage Database [29]. Furthermore, the influence of the overall codon usage patterns of hosts on the formation of the overall codon usage of viruses, defined as the similarity index D(A,B) [36], was calculated as follows:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
